    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-08-12T04:54:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-08-12T04:54:00-05:00" n="683"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d683">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.7962/24: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Saudi Arabia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moose</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jidda</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-08-12T13:00:00+03:06"
                            >August 12, 1942—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 14—2:01 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>45. My 44, August 11th, 4 p.m.<note n="30" xml:id="d683fn30">Not printed.</note>
                    Shaikh Yusuf Yassin, Foreign Ministry representative, has returned to Jidda and
                    this morning the request was presented orally and jointly with British
                    Minister.</p>
                <p>A reply is expected in about a week.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Cairo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moose</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
